* Age-graded results
*When to use:       Use this to provide fair comparisons between runners of different ages and sexes, or to offer special awards (like "Best Performance")
*                   regardless of who crossed the finish line first.
*How to use:        - Ensure your database has Age and Gender/Sex fields populated.
*                    - Call the Age Grade Percent or Age Graded command followed by the specific distance file (e.g., AGEGRADE.5K)
*                    -Use Sort Down if scoring by percentage (highest is best) or Sort if scoring by adjusted time (lowest is best).
*   
